Enclosing class:
GoogleSettingsContract
public static final class GoogleSettingsContract.Partner
extends GoogleSettingsContract.NameValueTable

"Partner" settings, Actually this is the only settings table, and it gets used for general Google-specific settings. The fact that it's called "Partner" is just a historical accident.

Constant Field Values

RLZ

public static final java.lang.String RLZ
RLZ is a tracking string used for ROI analysis. It is similar to client id but more powerful. RLZ data enables ROI analysis in Google's distribution business (Toolbar, Pack, iGoogle). It explicitly ties the revenue received from distributed software to the expense of distribution payments.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

LOGGING_ID2

public static final java.lang.String LOGGING_ID2
The Logging ID (a unique 64-bit value) as a hex string. Used as a pseudonymous identifier for logging.

MARKET_CHECKIN

public static final java.lang.String MARKET_CHECKIN
Opaque blob of data representing Market state (installed apps, etc). Used to hand off this data to the checkin service for upload.
